Errors detected during execution are called exceptions.

The statements try and except can be used to handle selected exceptions.

> PROBLEM:
You are given an integer, N. Your task is to read N lines of input. Each line contains two space-separated values, a and b. FIND A/B

>SOLUTION:

n = int(input())


for _ in range(n):
    try:
        a,b= map(int,input().split())
        print(a//b)
         
    except ZeroDivisionError as e:
        print("Error Code:",e)
        
    except ValueError as e:
        print("Error Code:",e)
    
